CVE-2023-29404  # Go testing package, dev only

# Network related CVEs with minimal impact for our specific use case
CVE-2023-45142  # OpenTelemetry, if using minimal telemetry

# Docs site (Docusaurus) build/dev-time deps — never shipped in the statically
# generated production site. No safe upgrade path. Added 2026-06-19.
CVE-2026-55602  # http-proxy-middleware: runs only inside webpack-dev-server during local `docusaurus start`. Patched in v3+, which webpack-dev-server 5 is not API-compatible with. Absent from the static build.
CVE-2026-53550  # js-yaml: build-time frontmatter parsing via gray-matter@4 (latest, pins js-yaml v3). Input is repo-authored docs, not attacker-controlled. No js-yaml v3 patch exists; top-level js-yaml already bumped to 4.2.0.

# Note: Review this file regularly and update as needed
# Always verify that ignored CVEs are truly not applicable to your use case